{{Not to be confused with|September 21|qq=September 21}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月廿一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 21일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}} . == Events == * Year 1 of [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:October 30|October 30]] , [[1673]] ) – Due to the burning of the {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Palace|qq=}} , floods, and other disasters, the era name changes from [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun (Japan)]] to [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] . * Year 7 of [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:November 11|November 11]] , [[1854]] ) – The {{ill|Edo shogunate|ja|幕府|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo shogunate|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} orders two steam-powered warships, [[:en:Kanrin Maru|Kanrin Maru]] and [[:en:Japanese warship Chōyō Maru|Chōyō Maru]] , from the [[:en:Netherlands|Kingdom of the Netherlands]] . * Year 3 of [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:November 2|November 2]] , [[1863]] ) – Farmers in [[:en:Kamo District, Gifu|Kamo District, Aichi]] , [[:en:Mikawa Province|Mikawa Province]] , revolt to demand lower commodity prices, marking the first recorded {{ill|Yonaoshi ikki|ja|世直し一揆|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yonaoshi ikki|qq=}} (social reform riots). * Year 3 of [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:November 2|November 2]] , [[1863]] ) – The [[:en:Tosa Domain|Tosa Domain]] arrests [[:en:Takechi Hanpeita|Takechi Zuizan]] and other {{ill|Sonjō faction|ja|Sonnō jōi faction|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sonjō faction|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} members in a large-scale political crackdown.
== Births ==
== Deaths == * Year 2 of [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:October 22|October 22]] , [[1625]] ) – [[:en:Kikkawa Hiroie|Kikkawa Hiroie]] , first lord of {{ill|Iwakuni Domain|ja|岩国領|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwakuni Domain|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 岩国藩}} in {{ill|Suō Province|ja|Suō Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suō Province|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (b. [[1561]] ). * Year 1 of [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Jōō (Edo period)]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:October 23|October 23]] , [[1652]] ) – {{ill|Betsuki Shōzaemon|ja|別木庄左衛門|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Betsuki Shōzaemon|qq=}} , a masterless samurai (rōnin) (birth year unknown).
